50 Shades of White
collections.description:
50 Shades of White is a limited edition collection of 50 pieces that capture the imaginations of the many. The collection is by underground artist ZZBE, inspired by Maximilian Feuerring's experimental two year period prior to his first exhibition in Paris.

One piece will be released each month.

The collection:
Art is the same as life.
Treat colour like it is alive.
Black colour is not a tragedy. Black is space.
A beam of light will retreat into black but will always shine back from the shadows.
Appoint colour on black.
Colour is LIGHT and LIGHT is LIFE.

Maximilian Feuerring was spiritually drawn to Fauvsim, being part of 'the wild beasts', utilising emotions to build on distortions and expression. Maximilian Feuerring studied in Berlin, Florence, Royal Academy of Fine Arts in Rome and Italy and exhibited throughout Europe and Australia.

collections.name: Explorations Inspired by Miro
collections.description:
● ◉ ● ◉ ●

I am a creator primarily dedicated to music, but during the process of making an album in tribute to Miró, I discovered a new way to express myself visually. These works are part of a creative journey I never imagined, and now I want to share it.

Born from improvisation and imaginative freedom, my creations explore a personal aesthetic language while embracing Miró’s influence. The first pieces in this collection emerged spontaneously, drawn quickly with markers or mobile applications, capturing pure and instinctive moments.

Over time, I developed more elaborate compositions, experimenting with textures, colors, and symbolism. Both approaches coexist here, reflecting the evolution of this artistic exploration.
